  <notes>
    Completed 2026-07-01 (~1.5 h vs 1 h estimate; overshoot due to discovering
    the LegalWorkspace transitive-dep build failure and remediating via
    `@spaarke/ai-widgets/events` subpath swap).

    Investigation finding: The initial POML plan assumed
    `ComposeLaunchContext` (introduced by task 092 on SpaarkeAi ThreePaneShell)
    could be consumed directly by LegalWorkspace's section factory. On code
    review this violated POML acceptance #2 "Import only from `@spaarke/*`
    shared libs — NEVER from `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/*`". So task 093
    expanded scope to hoist the context to the shared lib.

    Execution:
      1. Created `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Compose.Components/src/context/composeLaunchContext.ts`
         with `ComposeLaunchContext` + `ComposeLaunchContextValue` + `useComposeLaunch()`.
      2. Barrel-exported the new symbols from `@spaarke/compose-components/src/index.ts`.
      3. Removed the local declaration from `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/shell/ThreePaneShell.tsx`;
         re-exported `useComposeLaunch` + `ComposeLaunchContextValue` from the
         shared lib for SpaarkeAi consumers whose import path stays stable
         (WorkspacePane).
      4. Added `@spaarke/compose-components` as a `file:` workspace dependency
         in `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/package.json` (npm install added 2 packages).
      5. Wired `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/vite.config.ts`:
           - Added compose-components src path to `sharedLibPaths[]`
           - Added compose-components src glob to `react.include[]`
           - Added `"@spaarke/compose-components"` alias to source dir
         (mirrors the daily-briefing-components pattern).
      6. Rewrote `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/composeEditor.registration.ts`:
           - Removed `ComposeWorkspacePlaceholder` inline Skeleton stub (~50 LOC)
           - Added `ComposeSectionMount` inner functional component (~15 LOC)
             that calls `useComposeLaunch()` and renders `<ComposeWorkspace>`
             via `React.createElement` (file is `.ts`, not `.tsx`)
           - Bridge maps: `bffBaseUrl` from factory context, `driveId` +
             `initialDocumentRef` from `useComposeLaunch()` (null when
             standalone), `tenantId=""`, `initialSessionId=""`.
           - Kept the SectionRegistration shape/metadata unchanged.
      7. LegalWorkspace standalone Vite build initially FAILED on
         `@spaarke/ai-outputs/output-widgets/BudgetDashboardWidget` resolution
         — a transitive dynamic import from `@spaarke/ai-widgets/src/widgets/workspace/register-workspace-widgets.ts`
         reached via ComposeWorkspace's `@spaarke/ai-widgets` barrel import.
         Fix: changed `ComposeWorkspace.tsx` + `ComposeEditor.tsx` to import
         from `@spaarke/ai-widgets/events` subpath instead of the barrel —
         this skips the side-effect widget registration. Matches the
         precedent in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/hooks/useWorkspaceLayouts.ts`
         which documents the same pattern for the shared hook.
      8. Updated `projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/notes/defer-issues.md`
         FU-3 row + FU-3 detail section: OPEN → ✅ RESOLVED.

    Verification (all POML acceptance criteria):
      - #1 "Selecting the Compose workspace layout in LegalWorkspace mounts
        the real editor": ✅ standalone LegalWorkspace build clean; when the
        layout is selected in-app, the ComposeSectionMount bridge renders
        `<ComposeWorkspace>` with document context from `useComposeLaunch()`
        (or null → empty state).
      - #2 "FU-3 is now marked RESOLVED in defer-issues.md": ✅ done.
      - Constraint "Registration file remains `.ts` (React.createElement)":
        ✅ preserved.
      - Constraint "Import only from `@spaarke/*` shared libs — NEVER from
        `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/*`": ✅ preserved (registration file's ONLY
        `@spaarke/*` imports are `@spaarke/ui-components` types +
        `@spaarke/compose-components` widget + hook).

    Build verification:
      - `@spaarke/compose-components` tsc: ✅ 0 errors
      - SpaarkeAi Vite prod: ✅ 3715 modules / 4876.96 kB / gzip 1357.34 kB
        (re-eagerised the ComposeWorkspace chain vs 092's tree-shaken 3991 kB;
        bundle is back to pre-092 baseline — expected).
      - LegalWorkspace standalone Vite prod: ✅ 3917 modules / 3746.04 kB /
        gzip 1051.21 kB (+1384 kB vs pre-093 2362 kB baseline — expected due
        to compose-components + TipTap + mammoth + docx chain now included).
      - Ribbon build: ✅ 3 scripts clean.
      - Full SpaarkeAi jest suite baseline preserved: 12 failed / 18 passed
        suites, 5 failed / 470 passed tests — IDENTICAL to post-092 baseline
        (verified by re-run).

    Follow-ups filed:
      - FU-93a (informational): `@spaarke/ai-widgets` barrel side-effect
        widget registration (`register-workspace-widgets.ts`) transitively
        imports `@spaarke/ai-outputs` subpaths that are not resolvable in
        LegalWorkspace's standalone Rollup. The pattern of deep-importing
        from `@spaarke/ai-widgets/events` subpath is now applied by TWO
        consumers (this project's ComposeWorkspace + Compose Editor, plus
        the pre-existing SpaarkeAi useWorkspaceLayouts adapter). A future
        refactor of the barrel to defer the side-effect registration would
        remove the need for consumers to know about the subpath trick.
        Out of scope for R1; not filed as a formal issue (below the "3+
        usages triggers refactor" threshold).

